Although various antibodies targeting different viral proteins are induced after flavivirus infection, only two types of antibodies have been documented to provide significant protection: neutralizing antibodies to viral surface E protein (
 Crill and Chang, 2004; 
 Dejnirattisai et al., 2015; 
 Stettler et al., 2016; 
 Robbiani et al., 2017) and non-neutralizing antibodies specific for NS1 protein (
 Henchal et al., 1988; 
 Beatty et al., 2015; 
 Wan et al., 2017; 
 Bailey et al., 2018).
